Running the Application

Install Flask: Make sure Flask is installed. You can install it using pip: pip install Flask
Run the App: Navigate to your project directory and run: python app.py
Access the Site: Open a web browser and go to http://127.0.0.1:5000/ to view the front-end and http://127.0.0.1:5000/admin for the admin interface.





Enhancements
Database Integration: For a real application, integrate a database (e.g., SQLite, PostgreSQL) to store rooms and reservations.
Authentication: Add user authentication for the admin interface to restrict access.
Form Validation: Implement more robust form validation and error handling.
Styling: Enhance the styling with more advanced CSS or front-end frameworks like Bootstrap.
